				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I am a 12th level monk from qeynos and i just about choked when i read some of the info here on monks. let me tell all you monks and monks-to-be my info.<BR>
First off someone mentioned that agility will help you movemt speed. thats totaly false. all races run at the same exact speed depending on spells and lag.<BR>
my tips for your starting points are strength and charisma, and maybe some agility if you really want. str lets you carry more stuff. meaning you can stay<BR>
out longer and lets you do more damage and get more exp. charisma ups the prices you get from selling items to npcs and lowers the prices for buying stuff.<BR>
thats a very important part of making money, expecaly if you are going to make patchwork armor for money. and that whole deal on never wear armor because your<BR>
ac will go down over 15 pounds.. thats a load of croak.. yes your ac does lower if you carry to much, but it is NEVER low enough to make me regreat wearing full<BR>
leather and snakeskin armor!!! NEVER!!!! often when i'm done hunting i'm overloaded by 20-50 pounds and then i notice my ac is lower than it was before.<BR>
trust me people. wear armor. wear lots of armor. the more armor, the less you get hit and the longer you stay alive. nuff said!<BR>
and the single most important tip i can give you is this. travel the world. do it often, i am always going from qeynos to blackborrow to hunt, then to runnyeye to kill<BR>
some goblins when i'm sick of gnolls, then to freeport on to kaladim to kill some drakes, then crushbone for orcs and steamfont for the super cool mino slavers!. travel!<BR>

