			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I come before you to stand behind you and tell you of something I know nothing about...Well that last part isn't so true.  I am a 19'th level monk on the Tarrew Marr server and I would like to share with you the nuances of being a monk.  We are a pure melee, no magic, LIGHT WEIGHT class.  I would tend to agree that you would much prefer to weigh 40 with full leather than 2 in your boxers, however change that leather to full mesh and you will also notice a massive difference, in the ballpark of 30ac difference, just shedding the weight to below 15.  Secondly, it is not humans but rather monks specifically who recieve the Dual Wield skill more quickly than other classes.  A human warrior who gets dual wield around 15 will NOT be able to master it until level 20, but a monk will have mastered it by 15.  Be patient with this class, we do not shine until we get our dual wield and double attack up to master and pick up some magic gloves and full mesh or lupine armor, but once all of this is accomplished...well I can easily destroy a level 18 warrior with whom I often group, he uses a two handed combine sword and has full brass plate armor...your attacks will increase with each five levels or so- 9 damage until lvl 10, then 13 damage until 15, then 15 damage at four attacks- do that math, and add a strike from tiger claw for 13 damage...I would certainly put all skill points into agility and possibly a few into strength and/or endurance.  Agility is by far the monst important of all, but strenth will allow you to hit a few points harder at very high levels and endurance will up your hp by a few.  MONKS DO NOT NEED MONEY.  This is to emphasize that charisma is a waste of skill points, and that by the time you need a full set of mesh you will certainly have more than enough cash to buy it.  I have over 500 platinum sitting around waiting for judgemend day.  When I get a fine steel weapon I sell it to the nearest person for 4 platinum to save weight.  Get the idea?  Do not worry about money.  Level as quickly as possible and dont worry about traveling far until 17 when you will get feign death- it is a quite wonderful skill.  Having said my part, I assure you all I write is the truth and nothing but.. :)  Good luck and see you online.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
