	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				My first charactr i ever tried to play was a monk and according to most suggetions he was built very wrong. I put every extra point i could into stamina because knowing they could wear little armor i thought it would save his life one day more so than trying to dodge everything which doesnt happen often enough for my tastes. In the process of playing him i made some unique discoveries after talkin to to other monks. first of all with a 100 stamina i could pretty much wear what ever ever armor i wanted and only increase my ac as long as i didn't become encumbered. Yes to all you doubters out there who constantly heckle me and say i wear too much armor that is right I have testing lowering my weight extensively and it does not help my ac at all. The more armor i put on the better off i am period. I am the only monk I have heard of who can do this, which leads me to believe that perhaps the better your stamina the more you can carry without losing any ac bonuses. At my stamina (100 Stamina thank you) I can go all the way to barely encumbered in a full suit of leather and not lose a single ac point. Playing a high stamina monk is different but none the less quite useful. I suspect if more was spent into agility i may have a higher ac without the armor, but i get much better hp and i can carry a lot of stuff without any of the problems everyone with high agility faces. Any way if you ever build a new monk try it out and be ready for a very different experience.<BR>
<BR>
Hope you find this info helpful <BR>
<BR>
Liasom of the silent fist clan<BR>
&lt;bow and presents a open hand and fist gesture&gt;<BR>
<BR>
the silent fist clan will ever serve<BR>

