			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I'm glad I'm not the only one who's chosen to do something unusual with her monk.  I had actually started the original Hayley during the Beta and had recreated her when EQ was finally released.  Just for the heck of it, I put all my points into Charisma, going against any advice I had ever heard before. (I'd only seen the Str/Cha split mentioned abouve the first time today.  I found that for most low-ticket items (silver-piece range) I could buy and sell at equal prices with certain friendly merchants.  That little quirk allowed me to turn about 2 pp into 15 in one night by buying batwings for levitation and flight-hungry magic-users!  This allowed me to buy all the quest components necessary to get the white and yellow sashes, and two of three orange components - not bad for a 3rd level monk who'd never left Freeport!  Admittedly, I'm probably getting hit a little more than I used to, but my defense is improving faster!  Occasionally, I even use any blunt weapons I get as loot to LOWER my attack value and get hit MORE often to improve my dodge and defense skills (kind of like cross-training :).  So my monk is a little unconventional (but cute - 96 charisma!  Could there be another monk in the entire Norrathean Continuum so adorable?) but there's nothing wrong with that right?  This isn't MechWarrior, it's a ROLE-PLAYING game!  I want to get high level just as much as the next monk, or I wouldn't have come to this site, but why not challenge yourself?  &quot;Flow around conventional thought as the river flows around the stones.&quot;  My character isn't the most powerful, and I'm playing her as the Spoiled Brat of the Ashen Order for buying all her quest items, so she's going to serve her penance by gaining five levels in Misty Thicket.  After that, maybe a world tour. :)  With a little thinking, any character is a good one - that's my best advice to any player.<BR>
<BR>
Hayley - Ashen Brat
				</font>
			</td>

